1
00:00:11,500 --> 00:00:16,458
[gasps, grunts]

2
00:00:20,666 --> 00:00:25,041
[YUTA breathes heavily]

3
00:00:25,125 --> 00:00:28,791
[AKANE]
I... stabbed him.

4
00:00:28,875 --> 00:00:29,791
[All gasp]

5
00:00:29,875 --> 00:00:31,208
[RIKKA]
Hibiki!

6
00:00:31,291 --> 00:00:32,416
[gasps]

7
00:00:32,500 --> 00:00:34,000
[MAX]
Hang in there, Yuta!

8
00:00:34,083 --> 00:00:35,875
[BORR]
C'mon, hey!

9
00:00:37,125 --> 00:00:40,541
Sorry, but this had to happen.

10
00:00:42,041 --> 00:00:47,083
[AKANE] I know, I'm so rotten.
But there isn't any other way!

11
00:00:47,166 --> 00:00:49,541
[clattering]

12
00:00:51,500 --> 00:00:53,000
[RIKKA]
Akane!

13
00:00:53,083 --> 00:00:55,208
What in the world
is all the commotion?

14
00:00:55,291 --> 00:00:57,166
Huh? What happened?

15
00:00:57,250 --> 00:00:59,500
Call an ambulance, now!

16
00:00:59,583 --> 00:00:59,958
[RIKKA'S MOM]
Uh...

17
00:01:00,041 --> 00:01:00,958
Hurry up!

18
00:01:01,041 --> 00:01:02,333
Uh. Right.

19
00:01:04,458 --> 00:01:08,875
[RIKKA'S MOM gasps] What the--?
The phone's not working.

20
00:01:08,958 --> 00:01:10,125
[CALIBUR]
Neither is my cell.

21
00:01:10,208 --> 00:01:11,833
[UTSUMI gasps]

22
00:01:13,625 --> 00:01:15,208
Hibiki...

23
00:01:18,875 --> 00:01:22,291
[UTSUMI]
Yuta. Hey, c'mon.

24
00:01:22,375 --> 00:01:25,291
You're gonna be okay,
aren't you?

25
00:01:25,375 --> 00:01:28,000
Hey, Yuta!

26
00:01:28,083 --> 00:01:31,375
[YUTA]
Grid...man.

27
00:01:32,375 --> 00:01:37,333
♪


28
00:03:02,666 --> 00:03:03,916
[BORR]
Pull it more that way.

29
00:03:04,000 --> 00:03:04,916
[CALIBUR]
Hm?

30
00:03:05,000 --> 00:03:06,375
[BORR]
Yeah, so it's not caught.

31
00:03:06,458 --> 00:03:08,541
[MAX]
I'll close it.

32
00:03:08,625 --> 00:03:09,875
[RIKKA'S MOM]
Alright, I'm going!

33
00:03:09,958 --> 00:03:11,416
[ALL]
We're ready.

34
00:03:21,166 --> 00:03:23,500
[UTSUMI]
This morning, is like no other.

35
00:03:23,583 --> 00:03:25,291
[BORR] Every other time
a kaiju attacked,

36
00:03:25,375 --> 00:03:27,333
it all reset by morning.

37
00:03:29,125 --> 00:03:31,416
So what's gonna happen now?

38
00:03:32,625 --> 00:03:34,958
[CALIBUR]
H-His treatment is done.

39
00:03:37,291 --> 00:03:38,458
[UTSUMI]
Yuta.

40
00:03:38,541 --> 00:03:40,791
[MAX] Fortunately,
his vitals were missed.

41
00:03:40,875 --> 00:03:43,125
His life is not in any danger.

42
00:03:43,208 --> 00:03:45,000
[RIKKA]
I see.

43
00:03:45,083 --> 00:03:49,791
[UTSUMI sighs] Thank goodness.
Oh man, thank goodness.

44
00:03:49,875 --> 00:03:52,833
I tried over and over again to
get a hold of Hibiki's parents,

45
00:03:52,916 --> 00:03:55,666
but It's as if none of
the phones will connect.

46
00:03:55,750 --> 00:03:58,083
N-No. It's not just the phones.

47
00:03:58,166 --> 00:04:00,208
Looks like the net's down too.

48
00:04:00,291 --> 00:04:02,750
[MAX] It seems every form of
communication in the city

49
00:04:02,833 --> 00:04:04,416
is out of order.

50
00:04:06,541 --> 00:04:08,541
[UTSUMI] I wonder if it's
because those scenery-like

51
00:04:08,625 --> 00:04:11,416
kaiju all died.

52
00:04:11,500 --> 00:04:14,041
[MAX] If those kaiju
maintained the whole city,

53
00:04:14,125 --> 00:04:18,208
then the city and everyone's
memories won't be reset.

54
00:04:18,291 --> 00:04:19,500
[FEMALE ANNOUNCER] Dr. Amaji
from Internal Medicine...

55
00:04:19,583 --> 00:04:21,791
[MAN A]
Sorry, coming through.

56
00:04:21,875 --> 00:04:23,125
[RIKKA'S MOM grunts]

57
00:04:26,416 --> 00:04:28,583
Why don't you sit?

58
00:04:28,666 --> 00:04:30,416
I'm going to head to school.

59
00:04:30,500 --> 00:04:31,666
[VIT sighs]

60
00:04:31,750 --> 00:04:33,666
I guess students still
have to attend classes

61
00:04:33,750 --> 00:04:36,083
even during times like this?

62
00:04:36,166 --> 00:04:38,416
I'm just going to
check things out.

63
00:04:40,458 --> 00:04:45,416
[DISASTER SHELTER
ATTENDANTS chattering]

64
00:04:52,291 --> 00:04:55,375
[RIKKA] Looks like I'll
have to search for Akane.

65
00:04:55,458 --> 00:04:59,333
Even if she had her reasons,
what she did is unforgivable.

66
00:04:59,416 --> 00:05:02,541
[NAMIKO, HASS]
Hey! Rikka!

67
00:05:04,416 --> 00:05:05,375
[NAMIKO]
What a relief!

68
00:05:05,458 --> 00:05:07,416
I thought I'd never
see you again!

69
00:05:07,500 --> 00:05:09,750
[RIKKA]
Don't go killing me off now.

70
00:05:10,958 --> 00:05:15,000
[RIKKA] So, hey. There's no
way we can really know, but,

71
00:05:15,083 --> 00:05:19,333
lots of people have died up
till now, don't you think?

72
00:05:19,416 --> 00:05:20,583
[NAMIKO]
Huh?

73
00:05:20,666 --> 00:05:21,916
[HASS]
Up till now?

74
00:05:22,000 --> 00:05:25,791
[RIKKA] Uh, well. Like in
accidents or disasters.

75
00:05:25,875 --> 00:05:27,625
[HASS]
Yeah, that's a given.

76
00:05:27,708 --> 00:05:31,666
Still, I never would've imagined
that a kaiju would show up here.

77
00:05:31,750 --> 00:05:35,041
Kinda reminds me of
practice disaster drills.

78
00:05:35,125 --> 00:05:38,291
It's all so unbelievable.

79
00:05:38,375 --> 00:05:40,958
Yeah, but, hey. On the
plus side, those big guys

80
00:05:41,041 --> 00:05:43,500
appeared out of nowhere
and beat the thing for us!

81
00:05:43,583 --> 00:05:46,041
[HASS]
Yeah!

82
00:05:46,125 --> 00:05:47,541
[NAMIKO]
Speaking of which.

83
00:05:47,625 --> 00:05:50,166
How the heck did you know a
kaiju would come yesterday?

84
00:05:50,250 --> 00:05:51,125
[HASS]
Spill it.

85
00:05:51,208 --> 00:05:53,541
[RIKKA]
Huh? Oh I, uh...

86
00:05:53,625 --> 00:05:55,333
[NAMIKO, HASS]
Hmm...?

87
00:06:03,916 --> 00:06:07,958
[ALEXIS] Akane. I'd like to
discuss the next kaiju with you.

88
00:06:08,041 --> 00:06:11,708
There won't be a next one.
I don't need them anymore.

89
00:06:11,791 --> 00:06:14,458
[ALEXIS]
And why's that?

90
00:06:14,541 --> 00:06:17,208
[AKANE]
Because Hibiki is...

91
00:06:17,291 --> 00:06:20,000
Because I brought
down Gridman already.

92
00:06:20,083 --> 00:06:22,666
[ALEXIS sighs]
But the trouble is...

93
00:06:22,750 --> 00:06:26,083
It seems that Anti has become
the next Gridman in line.

94
00:06:26,166 --> 00:06:29,833
There's still a need
for kaiju after all.

95
00:06:29,916 --> 00:06:32,583
Your kaiju, that is.

96
00:06:32,666 --> 00:06:35,208
[AKANE]
I can't make kaiju anymore.

97
00:06:35,291 --> 00:06:38,250
[ALEXIS sighs]
Is that so?

98
00:06:40,583 --> 00:06:44,250
[ALEXIS] So be it.
I'll use what's available.

99
00:06:46,833 --> 00:06:51,791
[KAIJU roaring]

100
00:06:55,541 --> 00:06:58,166
[HASS]
Whoa, some more kaiju appeared!

101
00:06:58,250 --> 00:07:00,875
[NAMIKO]
It's a bunch of 'em!

102
00:07:00,958 --> 00:07:03,833
[RIKKA]
Sorry, I've gotta go!

103
00:07:03,916 --> 00:07:06,916
[NAMIKO] That girl. You know
she's hiding something.

104
00:07:07,000 --> 00:07:09,750
[HASS] Maybe, but you shouldn't
just assume that's a bad thing.

105
00:07:09,833 --> 00:07:11,541
If there's something
she's not telling us,

106
00:07:11,625 --> 00:07:14,583
that means Rikka thinks
it's better left unsaid.

107
00:07:14,666 --> 00:07:17,125
You sure have a way of
seeing things, Hass.

108
00:07:17,208 --> 00:07:19,291
[HASS]
That's because I'm her friend.

109
00:07:19,375 --> 00:07:21,166
[NAMIKO]
Because of that?

110
00:07:23,208 --> 00:07:24,166
[HASS]
Yup.

111
00:07:29,041 --> 00:07:30,708
I thought you'd already be gone.

112
00:07:30,791 --> 00:07:32,458
They're saying
they can't do it.

113
00:07:32,541 --> 00:07:33,958
Go out and fight, I mean.

114
00:07:34,041 --> 00:07:35,208
[RIKKA gasps]

115
00:07:35,291 --> 00:07:38,500
The power we have exists
only because of Gridman.

116
00:07:38,583 --> 00:07:41,708
Until Yuta wakes up,
Gridman won't.

117
00:07:41,791 --> 00:07:43,416
[footsteps]

118
00:07:43,500 --> 00:07:46,708
[ANTI] You choose to do nothing,
thinking nothing can be done.

119
00:07:46,791 --> 00:07:48,083
[RIKKA]
Anti?

120
00:07:48,166 --> 00:07:49,833
Uh, you know him?

121
00:07:49,916 --> 00:07:51,083
[MAX]
What do you want?

122
00:07:51,166 --> 00:07:55,333
[UTSUMI gasps]
You all know him? Who is this?

123
00:07:55,416 --> 00:07:58,208
He's a kaiju that goes around
pretending to be human.

124
00:07:58,291 --> 00:07:59,416
[RIKKA, UTSUMI]
Huh?

125
00:07:59,500 --> 00:08:01,791
The one that is always
getting in our way!

126
00:08:01,875 --> 00:08:03,458
Seriously?

127
00:08:03,541 --> 00:08:05,833
He's a kaiju?

128
00:08:05,916 --> 00:08:08,125
Not anymore.
I'm no longer a kaiju.

129
00:08:08,208 --> 00:08:09,916
Oh wow, is that right?

130
00:08:10,000 --> 00:08:14,250
The thing is, no matter what,
I won't accept you as Gridman.

131
00:08:15,916 --> 00:08:17,375
[RIKKA'S MOM grunts]

132
00:08:20,458 --> 00:08:25,125
Is it true? Are you that
copycat kaiju we keep seeing?

133
00:08:25,208 --> 00:08:28,250
Who the hell are you?

134
00:08:28,333 --> 00:08:31,041
A normal person.

135
00:08:31,125 --> 00:08:33,875
One of the many you
crush under your feet.

136
00:08:33,958 --> 00:08:36,625
I represent the people.

137
00:08:36,708 --> 00:08:39,958
Whatever. If I watch
my step, I can't fight.

138
00:08:40,041 --> 00:08:41,375
[gasps]

139
00:08:43,833 --> 00:08:47,208
It must be my lucky day getting
to meet a kaiju in person.

140
00:08:47,291 --> 00:08:51,166
Lemme guess, you've come
to apologize to us?

141
00:08:51,250 --> 00:08:52,875
What's apologize mean?

142
00:08:52,958 --> 00:08:56,541
[UTSUMI gasps]
Want me to show you?

143
00:08:57,750 --> 00:09:00,375
Cut it out! This is a hospital.

144
00:09:00,458 --> 00:09:03,333
There are enough
injured here already.

145
00:09:08,833 --> 00:09:13,625
[UTSUMI] When kaiju run rampant,
a lot of people become victims.

146
00:09:13,708 --> 00:09:16,583
But... I...

147
00:09:16,666 --> 00:09:19,791
To think I enjoyed seeing
Gridman fight them.

148
00:09:21,750 --> 00:09:23,500
[UTSUMI]
I'm despicable.

149
00:09:27,625 --> 00:09:30,375
Nothing's gonna change the
fact that you're a kaiju.

150
00:09:30,458 --> 00:09:33,958
And because of you,
countless people have died.

151
00:09:34,041 --> 00:09:38,208
But, right now, there's no one
else around we can rely on.

152
00:09:38,291 --> 00:09:40,583
That is exactly what
I came here for.

153
00:09:40,666 --> 00:09:41,458
[ALL gasp]

154
00:09:41,541 --> 00:09:43,416
Paying my debts.

155
00:09:45,458 --> 00:09:48,583
[ANTI] I was taught
that's good manners.

156
00:09:48,666 --> 00:09:50,708
That's so polite.

157
00:09:50,791 --> 00:09:52,541
--[CALIBUR laughs]
--[BORR] Whoa, what the hell?

158
00:09:52,625 --> 00:09:53,958
I've never seen
him laugh before.

159
00:09:54,041 --> 00:09:54,750
It's gross.

160
00:09:54,833 --> 00:09:56,583
I think it's sort of cute.

161
00:09:56,666 --> 00:10:00,583
Alright, Gridknight.
We request your assistance.

162
00:10:00,666 --> 00:10:02,083
Who is this Gridknight?

163
00:10:02,166 --> 00:10:06,833
From now on, it's the
new name... of your new form.

164
00:10:06,916 --> 00:10:08,375
Is it?

165
00:10:10,916 --> 00:10:14,750
Wait up! Where is
Akane right now?

166
00:10:23,333 --> 00:10:28,541
[KAIJU roaring]

167
00:10:28,625 --> 00:10:33,583
[ANTI, KAIJU grunting]

168
00:10:37,125 --> 00:10:42,000
[ANTI]
Grid... Knight... Circular!

169
00:10:42,083 --> 00:10:44,916
[KAIJU groan]

170
00:10:47,083 --> 00:10:50,416
[roars]

171
00:10:50,500 --> 00:10:52,250
[ANTI shouts]

172
00:10:52,333 --> 00:10:55,000
[KAIJU C groans]

173
00:10:56,250 --> 00:10:58,625
[ANTI shouts]

174
00:10:58,708 --> 00:11:01,916
[KAIJU A groans]

175
00:11:03,625 --> 00:11:05,166
Okay, he's pretty good.

176
00:11:05,250 --> 00:11:07,791
But there's just too many
enemies for him to handle.

177
00:11:07,875 --> 00:11:09,833
Alright. So what
would happen now

178
00:11:09,916 --> 00:11:12,666
if this were actually a
part of the Ultra series?

179
00:11:14,125 --> 00:11:15,875
What the heck?

180
00:11:22,625 --> 00:11:24,750
What's even the
point of fighting?

181
00:11:24,833 --> 00:11:27,666
[FEMALE NURSE] Kanesue?
Is Yuichiro Kanesue here?

182
00:11:27,750 --> 00:11:30,875
[MAX] I wonder.
Why won't Yuta wake up?

183
00:11:30,958 --> 00:11:33,416
[RIKKA'S MOM]
Hypovolemic shock maybe?

184
00:11:33,500 --> 00:11:36,166
Though, the doctor was saying
it's absurd for that to cause

185
00:11:36,250 --> 00:11:38,750
a coma, so I don't know.

186
00:11:38,833 --> 00:11:43,375
[BORR] Hmm. It might
be absurd, but Yuta is--

187
00:11:44,958 --> 00:11:47,583
[RIKKA'S MOM]
Hm? Something wrong?

188
00:11:47,666 --> 00:11:49,208
Is that how it is?

189
00:11:49,291 --> 00:11:50,291
[RIKKA'S MOM]
Hm?

190
00:11:51,916 --> 00:11:54,333
We need you to come with us.

191
00:11:54,416 --> 00:11:55,708
Where are we going?

192
00:11:55,791 --> 00:11:58,333
[footsteps]

193
00:11:58,416 --> 00:12:00,666
Huh? What the--?

194
00:12:02,416 --> 00:12:04,083
There they go.

195
00:12:05,208 --> 00:12:06,833
[KAIJU roar]

196
00:12:06,916 --> 00:12:10,791
[VIT] Up until now, Junk only
worked when Yuta was there.

197
00:12:10,875 --> 00:12:13,125
[BORR] If Junk and Yuta
are connected somehow,

198
00:12:13,208 --> 00:12:16,500
then Yuta should wake
up if we fix Junk again.

199
00:12:16,583 --> 00:12:18,541
[MAX]
Yuta and Junk are connected.

200
00:12:18,625 --> 00:12:21,541
So Junk and Gridman
being connected means...

201
00:12:21,625 --> 00:12:24,458
[CALIBUR] ...that Gridman
and Yuta are probably...

202
00:12:26,458 --> 00:12:27,875
[KAIJU groan]

203
00:12:27,958 --> 00:12:34,875
[ANTI]
Grid... Knight... Storm!

204
00:12:42,166 --> 00:12:44,791
[CALIBUR]
Hmm...

205
00:12:44,875 --> 00:12:46,833
[VIT grunts]

206
00:12:46,916 --> 00:12:48,958
[BORR]
Let's see.

207
00:12:50,666 --> 00:12:51,916
[RIKKA'S MOM]
Hm?

208
00:12:52,000 --> 00:12:53,958
[BORR]
Oh! Look what I found!

209
00:12:54,041 --> 00:12:57,375
That's an Optional 3-D Graphic
Animation Board, isn't it?

210
00:12:57,458 --> 00:12:59,875
Sixteen million, seven hundred
seventy-seven thousand

211
00:12:59,958 --> 00:13:01,625
two hundred-sixteen colors.

212
00:13:01,708 --> 00:13:04,291
I guess we're lucky this
place is a thrift store.

213
00:13:04,375 --> 00:13:05,708
It was thrown in the trash.

214
00:13:05,791 --> 00:13:08,333
The trash? You think
it still works?

215
00:13:08,416 --> 00:13:09,750
[CALIBUR]
We'll know in a moment.

216
00:13:09,833 --> 00:13:11,416
[RIKKA'S MOM] I hate to
break it to you guys,

217
00:13:11,500 --> 00:13:15,083
but that still counts as
the shop's property.

218
00:13:15,166 --> 00:13:17,458
That's why we had
you come with us.

219
00:13:17,541 --> 00:13:19,583
Cause it's something that
belongs to the shop.

220
00:13:19,666 --> 00:13:21,833
We'll take care of it.

221
00:13:21,916 --> 00:13:24,750
[RIKKA'S MOM sighs]
If you want it that badly,

222
00:13:24,833 --> 00:13:28,583
I guess you can just have it.
You did buy it once.

223
00:13:28,666 --> 00:13:32,083
Thank you.
We'll take it in due time.

224
00:13:32,166 --> 00:13:35,416
But right now, it's needed here.

225
00:13:40,708 --> 00:13:43,708
[AKANE] What's wrong with
a dream? Let's keep it going.

226
00:13:43,791 --> 00:13:45,250
Just like this.

227
00:13:45,333 --> 00:13:50,750
[RIKKA gasps]
I... have to go.

228
00:13:50,833 --> 00:13:52,666
Take care of Hibiki!

229
00:13:54,083 --> 00:13:55,500
[UTSUMI scoffs]

230
00:13:59,333 --> 00:14:02,833
It's just me. Everyone has
things they must do.

231
00:14:05,333 --> 00:14:08,250
But all I can do
is stay with Yuta.

232
00:14:18,500 --> 00:14:21,625
[YUTA]
Huh...? Wait, Gridman?

233
00:14:22,916 --> 00:14:24,333
[YUTA]
Where is this?

234
00:14:24,416 --> 00:14:28,291
[GRIDMAN]
This, Yuta, is inside you.

235
00:14:28,375 --> 00:14:29,708
[YUTA]
What exactly are you doing

236
00:14:29,791 --> 00:14:31,666
inside of me, Gridman?

237
00:14:31,750 --> 00:14:34,416
[GRIDMAN]
Why is Yuta inside of <i>me</i> ?

238
00:14:36,458 --> 00:14:38,791
[GRIDMAN]
Because you are me.

239
00:14:38,875 --> 00:14:41,250
Then Gridman is me?

240
00:14:41,333 --> 00:14:43,416
I shouldn't remember anything.

241
00:14:43,500 --> 00:14:48,916
It's not that I'm Yuta, but
Gridman dwelling inside of Yuta.

242
00:14:49,000 --> 00:14:51,500
Hold on. Why did you
dwell inside Yuta?

243
00:14:51,583 --> 00:14:54,500
[GRIDMAN] In Akane
Shinjo's world, he alone--

244
00:14:58,000 --> 00:15:00,416
There. That should about do it.

245
00:15:07,166 --> 00:15:10,666
[YUTA grunts]
Huh?

246
00:15:14,791 --> 00:15:16,041
You're awake!

247
00:15:16,125 --> 00:15:20,541
[ANTI pants]
Is that the last of 'em?

248
00:15:24,125 --> 00:15:25,458
[ANTI grunts]

249
00:15:27,250 --> 00:15:28,541
[ANTI shouts]

250
00:15:28,625 --> 00:15:31,375
[KAIJU D grunts]

251
00:15:31,458 --> 00:15:35,375
[ANTI grunts]

252
00:15:36,625 --> 00:15:38,666
[KAIJU D roars]

253
00:15:38,750 --> 00:15:41,208
[ANTI grunts]

254
00:15:41,291 --> 00:15:44,333
[KAIJU E growls]

255
00:15:44,416 --> 00:15:50,125
[YUTA] Utsumi, I'm sorry.
I didn't have amnesia after all.

256
00:15:50,208 --> 00:15:52,583
I think I never had
memories to begin with.

257
00:15:52,666 --> 00:15:55,375
[UTSUMI gasps]
What do you mean?

258
00:15:55,458 --> 00:15:59,708
[YUTA] I... I am Gridman
dwelling inside Yuta.

259
00:15:59,791 --> 00:16:01,083
Huh?

260
00:16:01,166 --> 00:16:03,208
Then I... This whole time,

261
00:16:03,291 --> 00:16:07,166
I was actually with Gridman
who thought he was Yuta?

262
00:16:08,541 --> 00:16:14,166
[YUTA] Yeah. Which is why the
real Yuta is still fast asleep.

263
00:16:14,250 --> 00:16:16,875
And will be until I leave.

264
00:16:16,958 --> 00:16:20,291
But before that, there's
something I must do here still.

265
00:16:20,375 --> 00:16:23,541
[UTSUMI] Still? You mean
keep using Yuta?

266
00:16:23,625 --> 00:16:26,666
What else is going to
happen to his body?

267
00:16:26,750 --> 00:16:31,291
Yuta was... Yuta was
stabbed by Akane Shinjo!

268
00:16:31,375 --> 00:16:34,083
[ANTI yells]

269
00:16:34,166 --> 00:16:38,666
[YUTA] Yes. Shinjo had
no choice but to stab me.

270
00:16:38,750 --> 00:16:41,625
She was driven so far into a
corner by the same world

271
00:16:41,708 --> 00:16:46,458
she made, that it was
the only option for her.

272
00:16:46,541 --> 00:16:49,875
Which is why,
There's something I must do.

273
00:16:49,958 --> 00:16:52,083
Something that only I can do.

274
00:16:52,166 --> 00:16:54,458
[UTSUMI grunts]
Stop it, Gridman!

275
00:16:54,541 --> 00:16:56,625
You're going to kill Yuta!

276
00:16:56,708 --> 00:17:01,500
Sorry, Utsumi. But I
have to be going now.

277
00:17:01,583 --> 00:17:04,125
You're not acting
like yourself at all.

278
00:17:04,208 --> 00:17:06,583
That may be so, but...

279
00:17:06,666 --> 00:17:09,000
[YUTA, GRIDMAN]
I am a Hyper Agent.

280
00:17:09,083 --> 00:17:11,000
I am called Gridman.

281
00:17:11,083 --> 00:17:12,458
[gasps]

282
00:17:20,750 --> 00:17:24,916
In the end...
I never did anything.

283
00:17:25,000 --> 00:17:27,625
[ALEXIS]
Very well done, Anti.

284
00:17:27,708 --> 00:17:30,500
However, it's about
time to end this.

285
00:17:34,333 --> 00:17:37,208
[KAIJU F growls]

286
00:17:45,708 --> 00:17:50,125
[YUTA pants]

287
00:17:50,208 --> 00:17:51,416
He's here?

288
00:17:54,833 --> 00:17:59,250
[MAX] Yuta. I take it
you're Gridman now?

289
00:18:00,958 --> 00:18:02,916
[YUTA, GRIDMAN]
That's right.

290
00:18:03,000 --> 00:18:06,291
Access... Flash!

291
00:18:10,000 --> 00:18:12,250
[MAX]
Let's go too!

292
00:18:12,333 --> 00:18:13,791
[VIT]
Uh...

293
00:18:16,666 --> 00:18:18,916
[BORR] I'm guessing
you saw all of that.

294
00:18:19,000 --> 00:18:22,208
Don't mind me.
If you have to go, go.

295
00:18:22,291 --> 00:18:23,291
[MAX]
Well, then.

296
00:18:23,375 --> 00:18:26,625
[ALL]
Access code...

297
00:18:30,083 --> 00:18:31,416
[gasps]

298
00:18:33,583 --> 00:18:36,791
[chuckles]
See you soon.

299
00:18:36,875 --> 00:18:39,750
Hey, look up there!
Something's flying!

300
00:18:39,833 --> 00:18:41,250
[HASS]
Nice colors.

301
00:18:43,125 --> 00:18:45,625
[KAIJU F growls]

302
00:18:48,583 --> 00:18:49,916
[ANTI gasps]

303
00:18:53,125 --> 00:18:55,166
[ANTI]
You're here!

304
00:18:55,250 --> 00:18:58,875
[GRIDMAN ] Sorry to make
you wait, Gridknight.

305
00:18:58,958 --> 00:19:01,750
[ANTI]
You're late, Gridman.

306
00:19:01,833 --> 00:19:06,791
[GRIDMAN shouts]

307
00:19:18,000 --> 00:19:19,583
[CALIBUR]
Take ahold of me.

308
00:19:22,875 --> 00:19:25,958
[ANTI]
Gridknight Calibur!

309
00:19:26,041 --> 00:19:28,583
[KAIJU roaring]

310
00:19:28,666 --> 00:19:30,375
[BORR]
Twin Buster...

311
00:19:30,458 --> 00:19:32,875
[GRIDMAN]
...Grid...

312
00:19:32,958 --> 00:19:35,083
[GRIDMAN, BORR]
...Beam!

313
00:19:38,791 --> 00:19:41,666
[roars]

314
00:19:44,041 --> 00:19:45,250
[ANTI]
Knight...

315
00:19:45,333 --> 00:19:47,041
[CALIBUR]
...Calibur...

316
00:19:47,125 --> 00:19:48,958
[ANTI, CALIBUR]
...End!

317
00:20:08,333 --> 00:20:10,500
What did you come for?

318
00:20:10,583 --> 00:20:14,000
I've been looking all
over for you, Akane.

319
00:20:14,083 --> 00:20:16,208
[AKANE]
'Cause of what I did to Hibiki?

320
00:20:16,291 --> 00:20:18,416
You do know if you had
just killed me sooner,

321
00:20:18,500 --> 00:20:21,000
none of this would
have happened.

322
00:20:21,083 --> 00:20:24,375
Don't say that. Why is that
all you ever think about?

323
00:20:24,458 --> 00:20:26,250
I can't help it.

324
00:20:31,500 --> 00:20:33,208
[RIKKA]
Hibiki?

325
00:20:33,291 --> 00:20:35,541
He's still alive?

326
00:20:35,625 --> 00:20:39,041
But how? I stabbed him though.

327
00:20:41,208 --> 00:20:42,541
[RIKKA gasps]

328
00:20:45,833 --> 00:20:46,875
[AKANE]
Don't follow me.

329
00:20:46,958 --> 00:20:48,875
[RIKKA gaps]

330
00:20:48,958 --> 00:20:50,583
I bet you think
I'm a stupid god

331
00:20:50,666 --> 00:20:53,375
without any control
over her world!

332
00:20:53,458 --> 00:20:55,250
Akane...

333
00:20:56,416 --> 00:20:58,750
Just go away and join
your friends already!

334
00:20:58,833 --> 00:21:01,458
It's not like this
even involves you!

335
00:21:02,625 --> 00:21:04,791
How does it not involve me?

336
00:21:04,875 --> 00:21:08,000
How could you even
say that? I...

337
00:21:08,083 --> 00:21:10,416
Unlike you,
I'm not a god, but,

338
00:21:10,500 --> 00:21:12,916
I still think of
you as a friend.

339
00:21:13,000 --> 00:21:14,291
[AKANE]
Yeah, but that's...

340
00:21:14,375 --> 00:21:17,958
You only think that because
I set you up that way.

341
00:21:18,041 --> 00:21:21,166
I made you believe
we were friends!

342
00:21:22,541 --> 00:21:25,000
You and I are friends, Akane.

343
00:21:26,000 --> 00:21:29,250
I don't need any other reason
to be born than that.

344
00:21:34,041 --> 00:21:37,666
[RIKKA] What do you
think of me, Akane?

345
00:21:37,750 --> 00:21:39,041
[AKANE]
I...

346
00:21:43,708 --> 00:21:45,666
[ALEXIS] Sorry to end
this pointless chat,

347
00:21:45,750 --> 00:21:47,541
but I must interrupt.

348
00:21:48,791 --> 00:21:50,291
It's the alien.

349
00:21:50,375 --> 00:21:54,833
[ALEXIS] Hurry it up, Akane.
You're needed after all.

350
00:21:54,916 --> 00:21:58,083
[AKANE] I told you,
I can't make kaiju anymore.

351
00:21:58,166 --> 00:22:00,833
[ALEXIS] Unfortunately, I think
you misunderstand me.

352
00:22:00,916 --> 00:22:04,500
I'm fine with you becoming
a kaiju yourself.

353
00:22:04,583 --> 00:22:05,625
[gasps]

354
00:22:05,708 --> 00:22:09,458
[ALEXIS]
Instance Abreaction!

355
00:22:17,041 --> 00:22:22,000
♪


